Sure! Here's a quiz on set builder representation:

1. Write the set {2, 4, 6, 8, 10} using set builder notation.
2. Write the set of even numbers less than 10 using set builder notation.
3. Write the set {x | x is a prime number} using set builder notation.
4. Write the set of positive multiples of 3 using set builder notation.
5. Write the set {-3, -2, -1, 0, 1} using set builder notation.
6. Write the set {x | x is an integer and -2 < x < 3} using set builder notation.
7. Write the set of odd numbers between 50 and 60 using set builder notation.
8. Write the set {1, 3, 5, 7, 9} using set builder notation.
9. Write the set {x | x is a whole number greater than 2} using set builder notation.
10. Write the set of first five prime numbers using set builder notation.

Answers:
1. {x | x is an even number between 2 and 10}
2. {x | x is an even number and 0 < x < 10}
3. {x | x is a prime number}
4. {x | x is a positive multiple of 3}
5. {x | x is an integer and -3 ≤ x ≤ 1}
6. {x | x is an integer and -2 < x < 3}
7. {x | x is an odd number and 50 < x < 60}
8. {x | x is an odd number between 1 and 9}
9. {x | x is a whole number and x > 2}
10. {x | x is a prime number and x is one of {2, 3, 5, 7, 11}}
